  <h3 class="subsection-heading">11.1.1 Including Eigen3 in C++ Packages</h3>
  <p>Include the following in the <strong><code class="path-inline">CMakeLists.txt</code></strong> of your C++ package.</p>

  <CodeBlock code={cmakeEigenInclude} lang="cmake"/>

  <p>For each executable node <code class="param-name ph-exec-inline">[executable_node_name]</code> in your package which uses Eigen3, include the following:</p>

  <CodeBlock code={cmakeEigenExecutable} lang="cmake" customHtml={cmakeEigenExecutableCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <div class="text-center" style="text-align: center; margin: 0.5rem 0;"><strong>or</strong></div>

  <p>If you have several nodes which uses Eigen3, you can use the following block for concision:

  <CodeBlock code={cmakeEigenExecutableMultiple} lang="cmake" customHtml={cmakeEigenExecutableMultipleCustom} showLegend={true} />

  <p><strong>Don't forget to modify your dependencies within the <strong><code class="path-inline">pacakge.xml</code></strong> of your package.</strong></p>

