  <h3 class="subsection-heading">11.1.5 std::copy</h3>

  <p>
    <strong><code class="path-inline">std::copy</code></strong> copies data between Eigen types and STL containers into an <strong>already allocated</strong> destination. Unlike <strong><code class="path-inline">Eigen::Map</code></strong>, the source and destination do not share memory. Requires <strong><code class="path-inline">#include &lt;algorithm&gt;</code></strong>.
  </p>

  <div class="param-list">
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-var-inline">[std_vector_variable]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">The <code class="path-inline">std::vector</code></strong>  variable used as a source or destination.</span>
    </div>
    <div class="param-item">
      <code class="param-name ph-var-inline">[eigen_variable_vector]</code>
      <span class="param-desc">The Eigen vector variable used as a source or destination.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h4 class="subsection-heading">11.1.5.1 Eigen to std::vector</h4>

  <p>The destination <code class="param-name ph-var-inline">[std_vector_variable]</code> must be pre-allocated to the correct size before calling <strong><code class="path-inline">std::copy</strong>.</p>

  <CodeBlock code={cppStdCopyToVector} lang="cpp" customHtml={cppStdCopyToVectorCustom} showLegend={true} />

